100767414582785968670<//user>
<Text>I didn't get around to writing this review until now eight months later, but here we go.

Our group of six people for a birthday dinner came into the restaurant and there was only one other small party so it was rather empty and slow. The service was good at first with a friendly male server for the first 15 minutes, but then he kind of just disappeared for the rest of our meal. I had to flag down other employees who were walking past our table multiple times to get napkins, water, and basic table service.

I don't write too many negative reviews, but this experience even now, almost a year later, still stands out in my mind. Management at this restaurant needs to better train their employees.

The food portions we received were rather very small, and the pricing was on the higher end. We definitely didn't get a great amount of food for how much we paid, which was about $25 per person for the hot pot special and it's not even bottomless! I ordered a vegetarian dish and I only got what I recall as four small/medium pieces of tofu in it.

We definitely won't be coming back again. Disappointed!<//Text>< Rate>

<Rate>4<//Rate>< Text>
My family & I have been coming to this place for years now. Eddie the manager is wonderful, helpful, and makes sure you're accommodated. This place does tend to get busy during certain days & times, so I usually call ahead to ask wait time. Services can be a bit lagging during very busy times so go on a day not too busy.Their food is great. Their single portion shabu is enough for two people but we also get their 2 for special. Angus beef. Corn Miso and sukiyaki. Dipping Sauces are good with the cooked meats & rice with the broth. Other side sides were good too. Appetizer calamari were a great size. Not tiny. Decent quality and thick. Haven't had anything that has disappointed us. Place is clean. Will upload photos next time.< /Text>

< review>
DO NOT EAT HERE.  THE MANAGER OF THIS RESTAURANT DOES NOT SHOW UP TO HIS JOB AND LETS FRESHLY HIRED WORKERS RUN AMOK.  I went to dinner the other day to only to be treated in the most horrendous manner.  My order took FOREVER to arrive to my table despite the restaurant being completely empty, and the explanation from my waitress was "oh, well we have alot of phone orders."  I let that slide.  Finally, we got our main course but never got our appetizer, despite having reminded our waitress numerous times.  We completed our meal, and instead of getting our dessert, the waitresa gave us our check.  We reminded her of the dessert, be we never got that either.  Finally, exasperated, i asked to have the items we never got to be removed from our bill, but our waitress informed us she couldnt because the manager was not in.  And why was the waitress a complete train wreck?  Because she just started working there!  So this so-called manager left this newbie employee along with another newbie employee completely unsupervised to run the restaurant!!!!   Unbelievable.  If the manager cant even show up for work and cant properly train employees, i can only imagine how this restaurant accomplishes more difficult tasks like keeping things up to code, assures that food is being handles appropriately, etc.  For your own safety, please avoid this place.  It is only a matter of time before this managers irresponsible behavior results in disasterous consequences.< /review>

< text>
We are very pleased to have found Myrtle Avenue Pet Center.  Moving here just at the outset of the pandemic lockdown, we needed to find pet supplies, a vet and you can imagine our standard poodle and soft coated wheaten terrier got quite scruffy.  We found all three at Myrtle Avenue Pet Center.  Both supplies and vet have been great but the groomers have really wowed us!  They took the notes of our previous groomer and a couple of photos and made the dogs look amazing. Both beasts are strutting around like princes now. Receptionist (gentleman) during most of the day, is great with taking payments in the time of COVID, bringing out the dogs and just being enormously friendly.  The young lady who checks in the dogs at 7:30am is either not a morning person or was just having a very bad day.  Interaction with her is short-lived and thatâ€™s a good thing.  By and large, the vast majority of the experience was fantastic and most importantly, our dogs returned home happy, healthy, well and looking beautiful!<//text>

<user_name>Shereen Skrypec< /user_name><Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
I brought my six-year-old on this speed boat adventure. It was super fun. At first it was a little intimidating when I heard the instructors giving details of how to drive the boat. But it really is much more simple than you think it will be. When we got off our flight at the San Diego airport, it is only an eight dollar cab ride away. We had a few hours before we could check into our hotel so we headed over and it was good decision!. They held our bags for us which was really nice!
All in all, a wonderful way to start our vacation< /review>

< Text>
My wife and I bought the Go San Diego card and we're trying to find something to do one of the mornings and decided to give this a try. We absolutely loved it. Looking back on our trip in the airport we actually felt like this was the most enjoyable thing we did while we were in San Diego. For those of you who are wondering how it works, we called and made a reservation for the next morning, which was really easy, filled out some waivers online, showed up the next morning and got to drive our own little speed motor boats on a tour around the harbor. It was such an awesome experience. We loved our guide Ryan, and everything we got to see and experience while out driving our own boats! <Review>The highlight of our day. This tour was exactly what we wanted, informative and entertaining narrative as we explored the bay, and between stops the thrill of racing along the waves. We've done this twice, and my wife and I both think it is a great value.

The staff is energetic and friendly, safety conscious and entertaining. The entire business is the kind that you want to see successfull.

Calm days are great for families and kids, but if you want a real thrill, go when its windy. The larger waves mean a thrilling ride that would put most rollercoasters to shame. Some boats are faster then others, but I'm not telling, this way I can keep them to myself when I come back!

Wish I could give 10 stars.</Review><pictures>None< /pictures>< Resp>

< Review>
Such a FUN way to see the city!  My husband and I have spent a little time on boats so we were super excited to do this tour.  Having our own speed boat to play around with in the bay sounded like the perfect way to spend an afternoon.  We did the 3pm tour which was the perfect time of day â€“ not too hot!  You get a quick lesson and overview of what you will see then you head out on the boats.  Its about a 2 hour tour around the bay and worth EVERY penny.  Our guide was Jason and he was fantastic â€“ very fun as well as knowledgeable about boats and the San Diego.   If you have two people that want to drive, you can switch Â½ way through.  This is a great activity for people visiting San Diego, or even San Diego natives like us!<//Review>

</dataset><record>
<userid>109782127815804642280<//userid>< name>
Nadja Volkmer< /name>
<date>1483471166746<//date><rating>1</rating>< Review>
Everything is fine, until something goes wrong. Your guide will loose its temper, shout and yell at you and at the end, he left us alone. Frustrating. Irresponsible. And for sure unprofessional and a no-go for this price.
1. If you are taller than 6', we cannot recommend this tour. We have bruises all over our knees.
2. If the two people in the boat are heavier than 400 lbs, we cannot recommend this. You will have to push your weight to the front of the boat for getting it "on plane", which basically means to get speed. In the beginning you will have additional weight of the full gas tank in the front to get you going. But at the end of the tour, your weight will not be enough to push down the nose of the boat and you will never get "on plane" anymore. The Guide (Bob or Rob) will make you keep trying, but if you have any understanding of physics, it is simply not possible anymore because of your weight and the mass distribution. Usually boats have a trim to adjust the motor to this weight distribution. But these boats are simple and small and don't have it or the guide didn't tell or know about it.
3. We had rather big waves. This also interrupts the traction to the water, which doesn't allow you to get speed. We ended up trying and failing.

The thing is, this trip is not a sightseeing tour. Don't expect that. You will be busy getting control over your boat and to follow the guide. He is alone in his boat and way ahead of you. They do not offer a two-way radio, there is only a speaker in the boat and while you are standing, leaning over the bow to get on plane, you will not hear a single word he says. After we mentioned this to him, he simply said "I know". How helpful is that? There are not even hand signals agreed on to have a minimum of communication with the guide.

When stopped the 2nd time, he told us that because of our problems in the beginning there will be no stop on the tour anymore. He more or less blamed us to ruin the tour for everybody else. Honestly, we didn't wanted to stop anymore and just go back. But guess what... Of course he stopped again, I ignored him first and got yelled at me again over the intercom... So I stopped and never got the boat on plane again. We were lying on the bow for the rest of the tour. Our knees hurt, our back and neck hurt. The guide was annoyed, rude and not helpful at all. If someone is yelling at you, that "nobody ever had these problems", I can tell you to read Yelp. There a dozens of reviews stating the same problems and the same carelessness. It was frustrating and nothing, we will recommend.

It might be a lot of fun, if you get speed. But there a a lot of factors, that could prevent you to get "on plane". And if so, it is no fun at all. The guide is not prepared for this situation and you might end up paying a lot of money for bad service.<//Review>

I've been getting haircuts at Alpha every few weeks for over 20 years but the quality and service has seriously declined.  It was much better when it was a few old guys who were very good at their job. The last straw: yesterday as I was walking up one of the new ladies, without even looking outside, flipped the closed sign and locked the door 15 minutes early because there was a crowd. I looked through the window but was ignored by the new people who don't know me.  As a customer I'm nice,  never complain and always give a $10 tip to my barber.   I'm sad to see it go as a long tradition but I won't  return to Alpha.  It's not as good as it once was.<//Review>

< Text>
We recently purchased our first house in the Bay Area -- a daunting task as many of you know!  Brady was one of the mortgage brokers recommended to us by our real estate agent.  After chatting with all of the recommendations, we chose to go with Brady.

The real estate market in the Bay Area is unlike anywhere else in the world.  It's so incredibly hard to get a bid accepted when you are competing with all cash offers.  Brady's team offers extremely quick closing which can give you a leg up on other offers.

After you're in contract, there are many ways the deal can fall through.  In our case, we had an issue with our appraisal.  Bay Area homes routinely sell for far over asking, but our appraiser only considered list price.  Here is where working with someone who is familiar with the local market made the difference between getting the house (really, our dream house) and having to back out of the contract.  Brady worked on our behalf to contest and get a new independent appraisal -- which came in at contract price (over 100k difference).  His team also advocated for us to get closing fees and expenses down saving us over 2,000 dollars.

Brady and his team are also extremely communicative.  He answers his phone, will explain any situation frankly with offered solutions, and happily answers naive questions.  I'd happily return in the future if we decide to purchase another property or refinance, without a doubt.< /Text>

<Time>1542218446691<//Time><Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
All mortgage lenders and brokers are governed by the same guidelines and regulations. However, not all Mortgage lenders and brokers are created equal. The KEY to a GREAT broker, as opposed to an average or good broker,  is someone who knows the guidelines well, AND someone who knows how to work within the guidelines and make the guidelines work for the particular circumstances and needs of each individual client. That is what you have in Brady Thomas.

I had a first and second mortgage on investment property I own in the San Francisco Bay Area. The first mortgage had a fixed affordable rate.  My first mortgage was owned by my bank, Wells Fargo.  The second mortgage was an adjustable, which had been bought by RPM several years ago. For a period of time, the payments on the second were affordable, due to government imposed low interest rates. Then the monthly payment on the second mortgage trippled due, in part, to increased interest rates, and due, in other part, to the nature of adjustable loans.  Thereafter, making the monthly payments became a nightmare. The rental income no longer paid for the two mortgages combined. I had to come up with the difference out of pocket.  That was eating up my savings. I was frightened that I would lose the property.

I spoke to a few other lenders, including mortgage specialists who worked at Wells Fargo. None were able to help. Then I was introduced to Brady Thomas through my property manager. Brady was a God Send. Brady was able to do what none of the prior lenders could do. He was able to combine my first and second mortgages into one new loan at a low fixed rate.  I now pay close to $1,000 less per month on mortgage payments.

The whole refinance process, from start to finish, took about 2 months. Throughout the process, Bradyâ€™s performance was flawless. If an obstacle arose, Brady would find a creative way to get through each and every obstacle.  He kept his promise and he delivered. He got me out of my loan with RPM.   He made it work. I am grateful.<//review>

< review>
Tasty food and good service. Late afternoon was lightly busy, nice. Oldies music playing on the radio and each booth has a silly book to read quickly while you wait. The Mexican burger was very good. The hamburger patty was thick, like handmade! Everything served was as hoped and hit the spot for a quick stop from driving. Nice, quaint diner. We'll keep it in mind next time we pass through.

Edit: This was the best burger we've tasted in a while. Really hit the spot.</review>

<Text>I purchased a package deal in which I'd get 3 oil changes for a discounted price from Mossy Nissan of El Cajon. I brought my vehicle in for an oil change for the third time about a week ago. A couple of days after, I noticed that the car was leaking oil. I contacted the service department to schedule a time for me to get the car checked out so that they could rectify the situation. I was scheduled but told that it could take 2-4 hours to look at the vehicle to fix the issue, which I found to be frustrating. It's bad enough that I had to wait 2 hours for an oil change on my initial visit. Disgruntled by the situation, I was determined to try to figure out was wrong. I noticed  that the oil drain plug was loose. I went to an auto parts store purchased a wrench and fixed it myself. A service bulletin was put out about the cooler kit needing to be added to my vehicle. which I was told i needed to pay for myself. I call Nissan of North America I received a case number, of course when i took my car in for diagnostic before even looking at the car the service writer said ohhh yeah new transmission. A $4,500, I cant understand, on a 5 year old car. On top of this they need to "keep" the car for additional diagnostic just in case. I was also told I would need to pay for my own rental car, Chula vista offered my when my phone call was transferred to the wrong location. I did receive a call the following day saying I needed to bring my car back for additional information, at this point i have not done so. Before leaving on the previous day, Other recommendation were suggested totaling 8,700. which I would need to miss work for as well as have a rental car for a week on my expense. My car is not ever worth that much. This is all very disappointing to me.</Review>

<review>This review is specifically for the service center: Robb and Elijah.
Went to my mechanic yesterday because my check engine light was on and showing a P0101 error meaning there is an issue with the Mass Airflow Sensor. Mechanic called Nissan to see if he could order the part, Joe in the parts department notified him it was under warranty and advised me to make an appointment ASAP. My mechanic cleared the error codes to turn off my check engine light and sent me on my way.
Showed up at 7am for my appointment this morning and left my car with Robb. Got a call around 9am that because the error code was cleared, Nissan could not service my car. At no point yesterday did anyone advise those codes needed to be kept in the system for it to be covered under warranty. Spoke with Service Manager Elijah who advised that there was nothing he could do until my Check Engine Light came on again. Now I have another problem with the tires on this car I have this car for less than two years and the tires on the front of this vehicle already need to be changed, thay have no thread leave on them. The other two  tires on the back are still looking brand new and I don't drive this car alot. If this car was a new car I should not have to change tires. {'time': 1580503343223, 'text': "Lincoln, thank-you for your feedback, we are so sorry to hear about your negative experience in dealing with our staff here at Mossy Nissan El Cajon. Yes, it is true that a vehicle can be sold as new with high mileage and may have it for a number of reasons. However, regardless of the mileage on your vehicle, your new car warranties (3 year - 36,000 miles and 5 year 60,000 miles) won't begin until you purchase the vehicle so you will have the full extent of the warranty until roughly 36,500/ 60,500 (to the exact mileage that you purchased it at).  Unfortunately tires are not covered under manufacturer warranties. What I believe the sales manager was trying to express is that tires SHOULD be rotated with at least every other oil change, but no it is not a given that service will do it because it is an additional cost, and it is not included in an oil change. Typically your tires should wear fairly evenly and that is why the manager was suggesting that the tire rotations most likely haven't been done like they should have been. My name is Ziba, I purchased my car from Mossy Nissan in El Cajon on ------------, when I purchased the my car it only had ---- miles and the sales person in the dealership assured me that the vehicle is without accident  and in almost new condition, he also gave me a Carfax at the time of purchase which showed no accident or issues with the car. <rate>1< /rate>< review>
My husband and I wanted to purchase a truck, we came here because of their reputation and the fact that I had to turn in my Nissan Leaf (2014) early because I had hit the mileage too soon and did not want to finish the lease.  So we brought in our Leased Leaf and our minivan as trade-ins for the Nissan truck we bought with David Gunn.  Through the negotiations I wanted to be able to turn in my Nissan Lease with no penalties as a good customer for purchasing a brand new 2017 truck.  This appeared to be part of the deal and we left both vehicles and drove away with our new Truck.  In June I received a phone call from the Nissan Leasing agency saying I owed them for several lease payments and they would go to collections within the week if they were not paid (the lease was up in May according to their paperwork but I left it with the dealership in March....)
I called the dealership and  spoke to Travis (Finance Manager)  and after some searching it turned out my Nissan Leaf was never "grounded" and none of the paperwork was completed so basically it was as if the car was still mine. Travis told me he would get Manny Jurado (our finance guy from the purchase) and David Gunn in the loop and ensure this was cleared up ASAP.  Nothing happened.  I have had to call them over and over only to receive promises of things being resolved when in reality all the phone calls and communication between the two companies has fallen on me.  When I finally got a hold of David Gunn after a promised phone call from Manny Jurado never came through David clearly had NO knowledge of anything that was going on. (this was over several weeks!)

To make matters worse they turned in the Leaf in June without giving me a call to see if I had the charger cable for the car which resulted in the Nissan leasing group sending me a bill for a missing Tool (no description and another phone call) for $896!!! Now after trying to drop off the cable which we had but did not know had not been turned in (major lack of communication) they turned us down and said we have to mail it back to Texas to get our record cleared.
I clearly remember the Manager that night we purchased the truck asking us if they will get a 5 star review....at the time we said yes but I am sure glad I waited....this team needs to get its act together and take care of their customers.  I am extremely disappointed with this bungled process and their lack of concern.  It's clear they only care about selling the cars and not about any issues they create for the customer after walking out that door.</review>
